: \"this ambition\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 428}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense we are, of course, really, really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 452}, {\"ngram\": \"any offense\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 493}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The apology marked a change of tone from the previous day's statement defending the provocative tableau of the Leonardo da Vinci masterpiece, a performance that spurred the hashtag campaigns #BoycottOlympics and #BoycottParis2024.\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The apology\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"a change\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 546}, {\"ngram\": \"tone\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 554}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous day's statement\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 588}, {\"ngram\": \"the provocative tableau\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"the Leonardo da Vinci masterpiece\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"a performance\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 674}, {\"ngram\": \"the hashtag campaigns\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 709}, {\"ngram\": \"#BoycottOlympics\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At least one company has done so.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 784, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"At least one company\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"C Spire, a telecommunications company based in Ridgeland, Mississippi, said on X it would remove its advertising from the Olympics, which is being broadcast by NBC on its main channel, its Peacock platform and its associated networks such as CNBC and USA.\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 1040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C_Spire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"C Spire\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://db